      "set:html": "<p>When building an Astro website with <a href=\"/en/concepts/islands/\">islands architecture / partial hydration</a>, you may have run into this problem: <strong>I want to share state between my components.</strong></p>\n<p>UI frameworks like React or Vue may encourage <a href=\"https://react.dev/learn/passing-data-deeply-with-context\">‚Äúcontext‚Äù providers</a> for other components to consume. But when <a href=\"/en/guides/framework-components/#hydrating-interactive-components\">partially hydrating components</a> within Astro or Markdown, you can‚Äôt use these context wrappers.</p>\n<p>Astro recommends a different solution for shared client-side storage: <a href=\"https://github.com/nanostores/nanostores\"><strong>Nano Stores</strong></a>.</p>\n"
